request.description:
Title: Create booking

Purpose:
Creates a new booking in the Restful Booker API. Use this endpoint to add a booking record with guest details, reservation dates, price information, deposit status, and any additional needs.

Request
- Method: POST
- URL: https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking
- Content-Type: application/json

Request body schema (JSON):
{
  "firstname": string,       // Guest first name (required)
  "lastname": string,        // Guest last name (required)
  "totalprice": integer,     // Total price for the stay (required)
  "depositpaid": boolean,    // Whether a deposit has been paid (required)
  "bookingdates": {          // Object with checkin and checkout dates (required)
    "checkin": string (YYYY-MM-DD),
    "checkout": string (YYYY-MM-DD)
  },
  "additionalneeds": string  // Any additional needs (optional)
}

Example request body:
{
  "firstname": "Nikita",
  "lastname": "Nigade",
  "totalprice": 111,
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-01-01",
    "checkout": "2026-01-01"
  },
  "additionalneeds": "Breakfast"
}

Successful response:
- Status: 200 OK
- Body: {
    "bookingid": integer,
    "booking": <same object as request body>
  }

Common errors and notes:
- 400 Bad Request: missing or invalid fields (e.g., invalid date format).
- 415 Unsupported Media Type: ensure Content-Type is application/json.
- This endpoint does not require authentication for creating a booking on the public demo server, but other endpoints (update/delete) may require an auth token.
- When testing, validate that bookingid is returned and booking fields match the submitted values.

Testing tips:
- Use different date ranges to check validation (checkout should be after checkin).
- Use the saved example to create a mock server if you want a repeatable response.

GET /booking — Retrieve list of bookings

Description:  
Returns an array of booking IDs and basic booking details from the Restful Booker demo API. This endpoint supports optional query parameters (firstname, lastname, checkin, checkout) to filter results by those fields. Use this endpoint to discover existing bookings before fetching or updating a single booking by ID.

Query Parameters (optional):

- firstname: Filter bookings by the first name on the reservation.
    
- lastname: Filter bookings by the last name on the reservation.
    
- checkin: Filter bookings with a check-in date (YYYY-MM-DD).
    
- checkout: Filter bookings with a check-out date (YYYY-MM-DD).
    

Response (200 OK):  
Returns an array of objects, each containing at minimum:

- bookingid (number) — The unique identifier for the booking.
    

Examples:

- GET [https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking](https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking) -> \[{ "bookingid": 1 }, { "bookingid": 2 }\]
    
- GET [https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking?firstname=Jim](https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking?firstname=Jim) -> \[{ "bookingid": 5 }\]
    

Notes:

- This is a public demo API; data may be reset or changed by other users at any time.
    
- To retrieve full booking details for a specific booking id, use GET /booking/:id.
    

See also: GET /booking/{id} for full booking details.
